author: @danigs007
text: A warning for "The Fall Guy" (1981) fans: Gosling is masculine but plays anything BUT Colt Seavers. Blunt is great but plays a character which is the complete OPPOSITE of Jody. So why steal the classic show's name & premise? Well, a combination or greed, laziness, lack of talent and cultural appreciation. They might as well called it "The A Team", "Mission Impossible" or "Star Trek". At any case you get two 40 year old actors behaving like two 14 year old kids using names of grown ups from a classic TV show about something else. They even changed the lyrics of original song in the name of political correctness. Shameful and completely unnecessary. (And This is how it's done: https://youtu.be/dj9ev40C30M?si=9QeyMQLBWixkKZXg )

author: @maysecondtwothousandeight
text:
This movie is perfect. It‚Äôs everything a movie should be. A movie that transports you and takes you on a ride of a lifetime. It‚Äôs so incredibly fun, exhilarating, inspiring, funny, massive, touching, heartfelt, awe inspiring, loving, daring, extremely well written and performed and made. It‚Äôs a complete and utter blast. I smiled legit the entire movie. And so far seen it twice. It‚Äôs everything a movie should be. Absolutely perfect for the theater, I wanna seen it everyday till it leaves. It‚Äôs just so cool. So fun. I absolutely loved the film! Loved learning and seeing this side of movies. I want to be a stunt performer now!

It‚Äôs become such a bright spot in my life right now.
I wish I could explain better how amazing this film is and how much it means to me.
The music is incredible.
The credits. The beginning, middle, and end. The twists. The action. The comedy. The romance. From the very moment it started (that pre film texting clip included!) to the very moment it ended. A perfect film.

I‚Äôm so grateful for these guys, for everyone who made this movie, for stunt performers. Thank you for stunts. Thank you for this. Thank you for what you do. Thank you for in a small part doing it for us. I‚Äôm eternally grateful. And thank you for this movie. It‚Äôs absolute blast and new all time favorite.

So‚Ä¶ Who wants to go stunting?
